#### gRPC Integration

**Why gRPC?**
• Efficient binary protocol (vs JSON REST)
• Strongly typed (Protocol Buffers)
• Bidirectional streaming
• Better for real-time data

**Challenge:**
• gRPC not directly supported in browsers/mobile (needs HTTP/2)
• Solution: **Envoy proxy** as gRPC-Web gateway

**Architecture:**
```
Flutter App
    ↓ (gRPC-Web / HTTP/1.1)
Envoy Proxy
    ↓ (gRPC / HTTP/2)
Python Backend Services
```

**Implementation:**
```dart
// gRPC client setup
final channel = ClientChannel(
  'backend.airvi.com',
  port: 443,
  options: ChannelOptions(
    credentials: ChannelCredentials.secure(),
  ),
);

final client = TrafficServiceClient(channel);

// Making gRPC call
final request = TrafficRequest()
  ..location = Location(lat: lat, lng: lng)
  ..radius = 5000; // meters

final response = await client.getTrafficData(request);
```

**Protocol Buffers Definition (example):**
```protobuf
syntax = "proto3";

message Location {
  double lat = 1;
  double lng = 2;
}

message TrafficRequest {
  Location location = 1;
  int32 radius = 2;
}

message TrafficResponse {
  repeated TrafficSegment segments = 1;
}

message TrafficSegment {
  Location start = 1;
  Location end = 2;
  int32 congestion_level = 3; // 0-10
  double average_speed = 4; // km/h
}

service TrafficService {
  rpc GetTrafficData(TrafficRequest) returns (TrafficResponse);
  rpc StreamTrafficUpdates(TrafficRequest) returns (stream TrafficResponse);
}
```

